<p><alert>I</alert></p>
<p>
	<dl>
		<li>
				<title>Inconsistent System</title>
			<p>
				An <em>inconsistent system</em><idx><h>system of equations</h><h>inconsistent</h></idx> is a ...
			</p>
		</li>
		<li>
				<title>Inverse Matrix</title>
			<p>
				The <em>inverse</em> of a matrix <m>A</m>, denoted <m>A^{-1}</m>, is a matrix such that <me>AA^{-1}=I</me> which is called a <em>right inverse</em>, <me>A^{-1}A=I</me> which is called a <em>left inverse</em>, or <me>AA^{-1}=A^{-1}A=I</me> which is simply called <em>the inverse</em>.
			</p>
		</li>
	</dl>
</p>

