<!-- %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%	O   %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% -->
<p><alert>O</alert></p>
<p>
	<dl>
		<li>
				<title>One-To-One (1-1)</title>
			<p>
				A function or transformation <m>T:V\rightarrow W</m> is <em>one-to-one</em> (also written 1-1), if <m>T(x)=T(y)</m> implies <m>x=y</m> for all <m>x,y\in V</m>.
			</p>
		</li>
		<li>
				<title>Onto</title>
			<p>
				A function or transformation <m>T:V\rightarrow W</m> is <em>onto</em>, if for all <m>y\in W</m> there exists <m>x\in V</m> such that <m>y=T(x)</m>.
			</p>
		</li>
	</dl>
</p>


