<!-- %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%	Z   %%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% -->
<p><alert>Z</alert></p>
<p>
	<dl>
		<li>
				<title>Zero Divisor</title>
			<p>
				In a ring <m>R</m> a <em>zero divisor</em> is a non-zero element <m>a</m> for witch there exists another non-zero element <m>b</m> such that <m>ab=0</m>. For example:
				<me>
					\left(
						\begin{array}{rr} 
							4 \amp 3\\
							8 \amp 6
						\end{array}
					\right)
					\left(
						\begin{array}{rr} 
							3 \amp -9\\
							-4 \amp 12
						\end{array}
					\right)
					=
					\left(
						\begin{array}{rr} 
							0 \amp 0\\
							0 \amp 0
						\end{array}
					\right)
				</me>
			</p>
		</li>
	</dl>
</p>
























